SIMPLE: sanded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanded
<hw>Sand"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered or sprinkled
with sand; sandy; barren.</def> <rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Marked with small spots; variegated with spots;
speckled; of a sandy color, as a hound.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Short-sighted.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sandemanian</ent>⟦br⟧
